:INFO
The Management Book That Did Not Lie to Me
Most management books describe leadership as a series of thoughtful decisions made \
by calm people with good information. Ben Horowitz describes something closer to \
the truth: decisions made fast, with incomplete data, while people are scared and \
the outcome is uncertain. I keep this book on my desk because it is the only one \
I have found that prepares you for the part of leadership no one talks about.

:NOTE
Horowitz is most useful when you are in the middle of something difficult.

:QUOTE [subtitle:Ben Horowitz, quotetype:PLAIN]
In good times you should do things that would be hard to do in bad times.

:JOURNEY
Reading The Hard Thing About Hard Things
Section
Applicability
- Peacetime vs wartime | 5 | Best frame
- Demoting a friend | 5 | Brutally honest | Honest in ways most business books avoid
- Culture chapter | 4 | Grounded
- Hiring and firing | 4 | Essential

:NOTE
This is not a book about success. It is a book about surviving the parts of building \
a company that are so difficult most founders do not talk about them honestly.

